Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: listening to an audiobook is just as good as reading it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: I have listened to many audiobooks and I have read many books.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: For example, I have listened to audiobooks while doing chores around the house, driving, and working out.
